Foursquare.py - v0.1.1

A simple python wrapper for the foursquare API.

http://www.foursquare.com
http://api.foursquare.com

More details:
http://ismaild.com/foursquare-api-python/ 

Created by Ismail Dhorat
ismail@zyelabs.net
http://zyelabs.net

Notes:
- arguments are required
- keyword arguments are optional
- the keyword is mapped to the key required by the foursquare API (except for set_pings)
- if authentication is required, username and password are the first two args
- use help(foursquare) for details on required arguments

Usage:
- import foursquare
- f = foursquare.Api()
- f.method(args, kwargs)

Help:
- View the docstrings
- import the lib, and then run help(foursquare)

API Methods defined:
foursquare.Api.test()

- Geo Methods
foursquare.Api.get_cities()
foursquare.Api.check_city()
foursquare.Api.switch_city()

- Check in Methods
foursquare.Api.get_checkins()
foursquare.Api.checkin()
foursquare.Api.get_history()

- User Methods
foursquare.Api.get_user_detail()
foursquare.Api.get_friends()

- Venue Methods
foursquare.Api.get_venues()
foursquare.Api.get_venue_detail()
foursquare.Api.add_venue()

-Tip Methods
foursquare.Api.get_tips()
foursquare.Api.add_tip()

- Settings Methods
foursquare.Api.set_pings()





